{"parse":{"title":"Duskwood","pageid":14049,"wikitext":{"*":"{{Infobox zone\n|name=Duskwood\n|faction=Contested\n|races={{Race|Human}} (3,000)<br />\n{{Race|Ogre|[[Vul'Gol|Vul'Gol ogre]]}} (1,000)<br />\n{{Race|Ironforge Dwarf}} (250)<br />\n{{Race|Half-Elf}} (250)<br />\n{{Race|Undead}} (250)<br />\n{{Race|Night Elf}} (150)<br />\n{{Race|Worgen}}{{Cata-inline}}\n|level=Scalable 20-60\n|loc=Central [[Azeroth (continent)|Azeroth]]\n|ss=duskwood.jpg\n|pop=5,000\n|ruler=Lord [[Ello Ebonlocke]]\n|government= Elected Magistrate\n|capital= [[Darkshire]] (3,500)\n|affiliation= [[Alliance]]\n|major=[[Vul'Gol Ogre Mound]] (1,000)\n[[Raven Hill]] (20)\n}}\n\n'''Duskwood''' is located in the south-central part of [[Azeroth (continent)|Azeroth]], south of [[Elwynn Forest]], east of [[Westfall]], west of [[Deadwind Pass]], and north of [[Northern Stranglethorn]]. Technically part of the Alliance and under Stormwind's protection, its distance from the mighty fortress and its close proximity to more malevolent forces in the south and east make it a realm of horror.<ref name=\"Lands of Conflict 46\">''[[Lands of Conflict]]'', pg. 46</ref> Due to events central to the [[Scythe of Elune]], Duskwood is a cursed, dying land. Beneath the eternal blanket of darkness which gave Duskwood its current name, the Scythe's effects have transformed what was once a beautiful part of [[Elwynn Forest]] into a land covered in gnarled trees and inhabited by the hideous undead and extradimensional worgen, brought along with the black fog hanging over the woods. Ogres moving in from Deadwind Pass have brought up even more problems.\n\nLong abandoned by Stormwind, Duskwood is inhabited by a defiant people who still cling to their holdings in the face of overwhelming adversity. On all sides lurk dangerous creatures, from skeletal warriors and [[ghoul]]s to ferocious [[worgen]] and, before the [[Cataclysm]], some of the most powerful members of the [[Defias Brotherhood]]. The militia of Duskwood, known as the [[Night Watch]], patrol the main thoroughfare and protect [[Darkshire]], wary of anything moving through the shadows.\n\nThe most prominent geographical feature of Duskwood is an ancient and long-dead volcano crater. The crater teems with life, and features one of the [[Great Tree]]s with a portal leading into the [[Emerald Dream]]. The sleeping [[druid]]s' influence can be seen on the surrounding land, which is cloaked in a twilight quite different from the rest of Duskwood. The woods also feature several abandoned farmsteads, as well as the prominent [[Raven Hill Cemetery]], which holds the graves of the numerous people who have been killed by wild beasts and undead since the darkness fell.\n\n== History ==\nDuskwood was not always the way it appears now. Located in the southern reaches of the Kingdom of Stormwind, the southern part of Elwynn Forest was the location of two sizable towns, now called [[Darkshire]] and [[Raven Hill]], before the area was overcome by shadow.\n\nA night elf by the name of [[Velinde Starsong]] came to the woods carrying the [[Scythe of Elune]]. Unknown events occurred and the Scythe found its way to the mine now known as [[Roland's Doom]]. What exactly happened to her after that is unclear, but it is likely she was killed by something that did not approve of her actions. The powerful weapon was later found by a man who was part of a team of men who had entered the mine looking for the source of its darkness. [[Jitters]] picked up the weapon, triggering its effect of summoning. The mine was immediately filled with [[worgen]], who then proceeded to rip the men apart. Jitters escaped with the weapon, but was hunted by the worgen across the woods, which were steadily darkening with the scythe's released curse. \n\nIn an attempt to rid himself of their chase, Jitters disposed of the weapon nearby at the [[Yorgen Farmstead]], whereupon he encountered the [[Black Riders]] from [[Deadwind Pass]]. The riders slaughtered [[Sven Yorgen]]'s family in front of [[Jitters]]' eyes. The frightened man then escaped to [[Raven Hill]]. The darkness lingers in Duskwood, although it is unclear whether the Black Riders claimed the Scythe of Elune and took it with them back to Karazhan. Now the people huddle in former [[Grand Hamlet]], renamed [[Darkshire]], battling the undead and wolf men who inhabit the murky woods.\n\n{{Cata-section}}\nPerhaps the curse was enough of a travesty to befall Duskwood, for little happened to the land following the events of the [[Cataclysm]]. The worst that happened was at the [[Yorgen Farmstead]], where the Defias have mysteriously vanished. The farm is now populated by resilient [[Corpseweed]] and [[boar]]s. Sadly, it seems that [[Lars]] is no more, as he and [[Sven Yorgen]] were chased away from their camp along the [[Hushed Bank]], the small plot of land taken by [[Grave Robber]]s. Though the whereabouts and disposition of Lars are unknown, Sven has apparently been afflicted with the worgen curse and makes an appearance at [[Raven Hill]].\n\nRaven Hill is now a camp for the worgen affiliated with the Alliance and has been somewhat expanded with a [[flight path]] and [[Gilneas|Gilnean]] structures. The [[Unseen]] no longer haunt the buildings, and even [[Abercrombie]] has decided to move on, close to [[Deadwind Pass]].\n\n== Geography ==\nThe Redridge Range lies on the eastern border of this zone, as these mountains stretch from the zone of the [[Redridge Mountains]] to the zone of [[Deadwind Pass]].\n\n==Travel==\n=== Getting there ===\n[[File:Gryphon.png|right|Gryphon]]\n;{{Alliance Icon Small}}Alliance:From [[Three Corners]] in the [[Redridge Mountains]], follow the road south across the bridge into Duskwood. From [[Westfall]], by crossing the bridge to the east. Also, by swimming through the river south of Elwynn Forest.\n;{{Horde Icon Small}}Horde:From [[Grom'gol Base Camp]] in [[Northern Stranglethorn]], follow the main road north across the bridge across the chasm and right into Duskwood.\n\n=== Flight Master Locations ===\n:{{Alliance}} [[Darkshire]]\n:{{Alliance}} [[Raven Hill]] {{C-inline}} \n\n=== Adjacent regions ===\n{| class=\"darktable\"\n|-\n! Zone Name || Faction || Level Range || Direction || {{Alliance}} Access || {{Horde}} Access\n|-\n| [[Deadwind Pass]] || {{Neutral}}\n| 55-60\n| East\n| By foot east\n| By foot east\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| [[Elwynn Forest]] || {{Alliance}}\n| 1-10\n| North\n| By foot across the river; [[File:MiniIcon FlightMaster.png]] from [[Darkshire]] to [[Stormwind City]]\n| By foot across the river\n|-\n| [[Northern Stranglethorn]] || {{Horde}} {{Alliance}}\n| 25-30 || South\n| By foot south; [[File:MiniIcon FlightMaster.png]] from [[Darkshire]] or [[Raven Hill]] to [[Rebel Camp]]\n| By foot south\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| [[Redridge Mountains]] || {{Alliance}}\n| 15-20\n| Northeast\n| By foot northeast; [[File:MiniIcon FlightMaster.png]] from [[Darkshire]] to [[Lakeshire]]\n| By foot northeast\n|-\n| [[Westfall]] || {{Alliance}}\n| 10-15 || West\n| By foot west across the river; [[File:MiniIcon FlightMaster.png]] from [[Darkshire]] or [[Raven Hill]] to [[Sentinel Hill]]\n| By foot west across the river\n|}\n\n==Inhabitants==\n[[File:Beasts.png|right]]\n{| class=\"darktable\"\n|-\n! Classification !! Type\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\" | [[Beast]]\n| [[Bear]]s\n|-\n| [[Boar]]s\n|-\n| [[Owl]]s\n|-\n| [[Spider]]s\n|-\n|[[Spirit beast]]\n|-\n| [[Wolf|Wolves]]\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| rowspan=\"1\" | [[Elemental]]\n| [[Corpseweed]]s\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[Humanoid]]\n| [[Human]]s\n|-\n| [[Ogre]]s\n|-\n| [[Worgen]]\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| rowspan=\"4\" |[[Undead]]\n| [[Abomination]]\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| [[Ghost]]s\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| [[Ghoul]]s\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| [[Skeleton]]s\n|}\n\n==Resources==\n[[File:Trade mining.png|right]]\n[[File:Trade herbalism.png|right]]\n[[File:Inv misc pelt wolf 01.png|right]]\n[[File:Trade fishing.png|right]]\n{| class=\"darktable\"\n|-\n! Source !! Item !! Skill Level\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\" | [[Herbalism]]\n| {{item|icon=|Mageroyal}}\n| align=\"center\" | 50\n|-\n| {{item|icon=|Briarthorn}}\n| align=\"center\" | 70\n|-\n| {{item|icon=|Bruiseweed}}\n| align=\"center\" | 85\n|-\n| {{item|icon=|Grave Moss}}\n| align=\"center\" | 105\n|-\n| {{item|icon=|Wild Steelbloom}}\n| align=\"center\" | 115\n|-\n| {{item|icon=|Kingsblood}}\n| align=\"center\" | 125\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| rowspan=\"5\" | [[Mining]]\n| {{item|icon=|Copper Ore}} from Copper Veins\n| align=\"center\" | 1\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| {{item|icon=|Tin Ore}} from Tin Veins\n| align=\"center\" | 65\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| {{item|icon=|Silver Ore}} from Silver Veins\n| align=\"center\" | 75\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| {{item|icon=|Iron Ore}} from Iron Deposits\n| align=\"center\" | 125\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| {{item|icon=|Gold Ore}} from Gold Veins\n| align=\"center\" | 155\n|}\n{| class=\"darktable\"\n|-\n! Source !! Item\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" | [[Cloth]] (Drop)\n| {{item|icon=|Linen Cloth}}\n|-\n| {{item|icon=|Wool Cloth}}\n|-\n| {{item|icon=|Silk Cloth}}\n|-\n| {{item|icon=|Spider's Silk}}\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[Skinning]]\n| {{item|icon=|Light Leather}}\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| {{item|icon=|Medium Leather}}\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| {{item|icon=|Heavy Leather}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Fishing]] (Pools)\n| {{item|icon=|Sagefish}}\n|-\n| {{profIcon|Fishing}}[[Floating Debris]]\n|}\n\n== Notable characters ==\n{{main|Duskwood NPCs}}\n\nDuskwood is home to several humans of note. In Darkshire, [[Commander Althea Ebonlocke]] sends willing adventurers to battle back the evil denizens of the dark woods. At the northwestern corner of the forest, [[Sven Yorgen]] directs budding heroes to uncover a magical weapon with which to weaken the evil [[Morbent Fel]] located in his dark house on Forlorn Rowe. And at Raven Hill, a frightened man nicknamed [[Jitters]] hides from his dark past.\n\n== Quests ==\n{{main|Duskwood quests}}\n\n==Areas of interest==\n[[File:Inv misc idol 05.png|right]] \n===Maps===\n<gallery>\nImage:WorldMap-Duskwood-old.jpg|Map of Duskwood, pre-Cataclysm\nImage:WorldMap-Duskwood.jpg|Map of Duskwood, post-Cataclysm (Current)\n</gallery>\n\n===Subzones===\n{| class=\"darktable\"\n|-\n!{{wow-inline}} In-game\n|-\n|{{Duskwood|subzonesonly=}}\n|-\n||\n----\n'''[[Lore]]'''\n\n[[Tanglefoot Junction]] \u2022 [[Knight's Hollow]]\n|}\n{{clear|both}}\n\n==Additional information==\n[[File:Trade_archaeology_highborne_scroll.png|right]] \n;Treasure of Duskwood\nDuskwood is rather unique with regard to its [[chest|treasure chests]].  In most zones on Azeroth, treasure chests spawn next to or inside buildings or ruins, often in the middle of a camp of hostile mobs and virtually always with at least one mob guarding it.  In Duskwood, especially north of the main road that cuts across the zone, treasure chests will spawn randomly in the forest next to trees and often without any hostile mobs near them.  Chests also spawn at ruined buildings in [[Brightwood Grove]] and at the remains of a small house near [[Addle's Stead]], generally with only a single hostile beast wandering nearby and it is fairly easy to loot the chests without drawing aggro.  For an Alliance character in a level range of mid-to-high 20s, treasure hunting in Duskwood can be a fun and profitable adventure.\n\n;Lore\n{{Warcraft III}}\nBeasts with green scales inhabit this jungle, making it hard to spot them. The tileset is called \"Ashenvale\".<ref name=\"Official Blizzard Warcraft 3 multiplayer maps from the game and its expansion.\">'Official Blizzard Warcraft 3 multiplayer maps from the game and its expansion.''<nowiki/>''</ref>\n\n==Media==\n===Images===\n<gallery position=\"center\" captionalign=\"center\">\nRoland's Doom.jpg|Roland's Doom\nDuskwood day.jpg|Duskwood at day\nRaven Hill Cemetery.jpg|Raven Hill Cemetery\nRotting_Orchard.jpeg|A worgen in the Rotting Orchard\nThe Rotting Orchard.jpg|The Rotting Orchard\nForlorn Rowe.jpg|Forlorn Rowe\nDarkshire.jpg|Darkshire\n</gallery>\n\n===Videos===\n<gallery position=\"center\" captionalign=\"center\">\nDuskwood HD - World of Warcraft Cataclysm\nCataclysm - Duskwood Overview\n</gallery>\n\n==Patch changes==\n*{{Patch 4.0.3a|note=Flight path added to Raven Hill; now a hub.}}\n*{{Patch 1.8.0|note=A Graveyard has been added to Duskwood at Raven Hill Cemetery.}}\n*{{Patch 1.3.0|note=\n**Players will no longer fall through the ground in a cave location in Duskwood.\n**Players can no longer gain access to Zul'Gurub through Duskwood.}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n<!-- Read http://www.wowwiki.com/WoWWiki:External_links before posting your links here.\nLinks that do not conform to the rules will be DELETED.\nRepeat violations may result in a BAN.\nHave a nice day. :) -->\n{{elinks-zone|10}}\n\n\n{{Duskwood}}\n{{Kingdom of Stormwind}}\n{{Eastern Kingdoms}}\n\n[[es:Bosque del Ocaso]]\n[[fr:Bois de la P\u00e9nombre]]\n[[nl:Duskwood]]\n[[pl:Duskwood]]\n[[ru:\u0421\u0443\u043c\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0447\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u043b\u0435\u0441]]\n[[Category:Woods]]\n[[Category:Duskwood| ]]\n[[Category:Human territories]]\n[[Category:Warcraft III maps]]"}}}